The paper discusses neural network-based methods for generating question-answer pairs from text, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Specifically, the paper focuses on question generation, which is a subfield of NLP that involves generating questions from text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP research. Additionally, the paper uses sequence to sequence models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI and cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of handling rare words, which is a problem in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses global attention and answer encoding, which are techniques commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
